description._content: Catalog #: 15_001431 Title: Detroit Lockheed YP-24 ADDITIONAL INFORMATION: Detroit Lockheed YP-24. First aircraft to bear the name Lockheed. Lockheed-Detroit XP-900 (later redesignated YP-24), crashed on a test flight from Wright Field, Ohio on October 19, 1931, pilot parachuted to safety. Collection: Charles M. Daniels Collection Photo Album Name: U.S Manufacturers IV, G to L Page #: 29 Tags: Detroit Lockheed YP-24 PUBLIC COMMONS.SOURCE INSTITUTION: San Diego Air and Space Museum Archive
